@Bill Slang terms for money... yeah  there's a few. For instance:

Dooteroomus, John-Davis (or ready-John), ginglers, root of all evil, spondulicks, ooftish, legem pone, palm-oil, shadscales, nuggets, rhino, portcullis, sinews of war, shin-plasters, mammon, mazda-caroon, old Mr. Gory, canary, new-hat, thick-'un, loonslate, Abraham's willing (that one is rhyming slang for "shilling"), hog-and-a-kye, yellow-George... 

